Process Data.content:
# Data Processing Node

## Purpose
This node handles data transformation and cleaning operations.

## Configuration
- **Input Format**: CSV, JSON
- **Processing Type**: ETL (Extract, Transform, Load)
- **Output Format**: Processed JSON

## Implementation Notes
```javascript
// Sample transformation logic
function processData(input) {
  return input
    .filter(item => item.isValid)
    .map(item => ({
      ...item,
      processed: true,
      timestamp: new Date().toISOString()
    }));
}
```

## Performance Considerations
- Batch size: 1000 records
- Memory usage: ~50MB
- Average processing time: 2.3s

## Testing
- [x] Unit tests passed
- [x] Integration tests passed
- [ ] Performance benchmarks

Output.content:
# Output Node

## Purpose
Exports processed data to various formats and destinations.

## Supported Outputs
- File exports (JSON, CSV, XML)
- Database connections
- API endpoints
- Cloud storage

## Configuration Examples

### File Export
```json
{
  "type": "file",
  "format": "json",
  "path": "/exports/data.json",
  "compression": "gzip"
}
```

### Database Export
```json
{
  "type": "database",
  "connection": "postgresql://...",
  "table": "processed_data",
  "mode": "insert"
}
```

## Monitoring
- Export success rate: 99.2%
- Average export time: 1.8s
- Last successful export: 2024-01-20T15:45:00Z
